1. Stavila sam *masku* na lice pre ulaska u prodavnicu. (I put on a *mask* on my face before entering the store.)
2. Zašto ne nosiš *masku* na autobusu? (Why aren't you wearing a *mask* on the bus?)
3. Ukoliko ne nosite *masku* u zatvorenom prostoru, možete biti kažnjeni. (If you don't wear a *mask* indoors, you can be fined.)
4. *Maska* koju si kupila je prevelika za moje lice. (The *mask* you bought is too big for my face.)
5. Ne volim da nosim *maske* za spavanje, osećam se nelagodno. (I don't like wearing *eye masks* for sleeping, I feel uncomfortable.)
6. Ukoliko želite da se prijavite za radionicu, potrebno je da popunite *masku* za prijavu. (If you want to apply for the workshop, you need to fill out an *application form*.)
7. *Maska* koju su koristili glumci bila je jako efektna. (The *prop* mask used by the actors was very effective.)
8. Preporučujem da koristite *masku* za kosu kako bi bila mekša i sjajnija. (I recommend using a *hair mask* to make it softer and shinier.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "maska" can refer to both a medical mask (for example, during the COVID-19 pandemic) and a prop mask used in theater or film, while "masku" is the accusative case form of "maska". The word "maske" in Serbian can also refer to eye masks or other types of masks (such as hair masks or face masks), and "masku" is the accusative case form of "maske".